The paper discusses the use of MDPC codes in cryptography, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The attack and defense mechanisms proposed in the paper involve the properties of the parity-check matrix of the codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the decoding failure probability of the codes, which is a measure of their reliability and can be relevant to topics such as error-correcting codes (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI).
